{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "25f91db2495688a6", "candidate": {"id": "cand-010", "name": "Kieran Walsh", "raw_cv": "KIERAN WALSH\nkieran.walsh@email.com | London, UK\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 5 years of experience across e-commerce, media, and fintech sectors. Proficient in Python, dbt, and Snowflake. Strong background in data product development and stakeholder management.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Data Engineer \u2014 Deliveroo, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained dbt models for the rider and restaurant analytics platform\n- Designed Airflow pipelines for daily reporting and product analytics\n- Collaborated with product and finance teams to define key metrics\n- Refactored legacy ETL jobs in Python, reducing runtime by 40%\n\nData Engineer \u2014 The Guardian, London (2019\u20132021)\n- Built audience and content analytics pipelines in BigQuery\n- Worked on subscriber lifetime value modelling data feeds\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, BigQuery, Airflow, Docker, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Statistics \u2014 University of Warwick (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Irish dual national)", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer with five years of experience across some of London's most interesting data-intensive companies \u2014 Deliveroo and The Guardian. I love building data infrastructure that actually gets used and trusted by stakeholders. Strong in dbt, Python, and Snowflake. Interested in my next challenge \u2014 ideally somewhere with interesting data and a healthy work-life balance culture.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Kieran, what draws you to financial data engineering after time in media and e-commerce?\n\nKieran: I'm genuinely attracted to the rigour of financial data. In media you can get away with approximate numbers; in fintech the reconciliation has to be exact. I find that challenge appealing. I've been picking up knowledge on the regulatory side in my own time \u2014 reading about CASS, MiFID data requirements.\n\nInterviewer: Good to hear. What about the five-days-in-office arrangement?\n\nKieran: That's the one thing I'd want to talk through. I'm fully committed to this role and the company, but I've been hoping for a four-day working week. It's been a personal goal for a while \u2014 I coach youth football on Friday evenings and having a compressed schedule would let me manage that much better. Is there any flexibility there, or is five full days genuinely fixed?\n\nInterviewer: It's fixed, unfortunately. The role requires five days at Canary Wharf \u2014 it's a team and culture thing, not just a policy.\n\nKieran: I understand. I'm not going to pretend it's ideal for me. I'd still be very interested in the role \u2014 I'm not going to walk away over it \u2014 but I want to be honest that it's a consideration for me.\n\nInterviewer: We appreciate the honesty. Let's continue the conversation. Salary?\n\nKieran: I'm at \u00a374,000. I'd be looking for \u00a378\u201382,000.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "BigQuery", "Airflow", "Docker", "Git"], "industries": ["e-commerce", "media", "fintech"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.5, "culture_fit_score": 0.5, "constraints": [{"id": "af9fd42e", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a374,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 74000.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "f30eab74", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation range \u00a378,000\u2013\u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 78000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "4d2eac4c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation upper bound \u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 0.85, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "0f3f25d0", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Prefers four-day working week; would improve work-life balance for coaching commitments", "canonical_key": "four_day_week", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.8, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "851ef115", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Employer requires five full days in office at Canary Wharf (fixed policy, non-negotiable)", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 5.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": null}, {"id": "4235dcb4", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "culture", "description": "Values healthy work-life balance culture", "canonical_key": null, "value": "healthy work-life balance", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.75, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "55b1ee8c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "domain_expertise", "description": "Interested in fintech and financial data engineering; attracted to rigour and regulatory compliance aspects", "canonical_key": null, "value": "fintech/financial data", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.85, "confidence": 0.91, "currency": null}], "discipline": "data"}, "embedding": [-0.036956787109375, 0.046783447265625, 0.045257568359375, -0.0083770751953125, 0.0252685546875, -0.025177001953125, 0.01128387451171875, 0.0438232421875, -0.0009050369262695312, 0.01422882080078125, -0.0116119384765625, -0.02978515625, -0.026641845703125, -0.01374053955078125, 0.0467529296875, 0.0477294921875, -0.034210205078125, 0.00897216796875, -0.03173828125, -0.0010404586791992188, 0.0220489501953125, 0.0075531005859375, -0.022552490234375, 0.02435302734375, 0.0261688232421875, 0.015625